    "what_description": "Cracca schiedeana is a legume species belonging to the family Fabaceae. It is an annual or perennial herb with erect stems, 30-50 cm tall, bearing trifoliate leaves with 3 leaflets, 2-5 cm long, and 1-2 cm wide. The leaves are glabrous or pubescent, with 2-3 pairs of primary lateral veins. The inflorescences are axillary, with 2-4 flowers in a raceme, each 2-3 mm long, with a purple or pink color. The flowers have 5 petals, 1 mm long, and 10 stamens, 3 mm long, with a calyx 1-2 mm long.",
