    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Cracca schiedeana are antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antioxidant activities. Antimicrobial properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of saponins, which exhibit inhibitory effects on the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. The anti-inflammatory activity is mainly due to the bioactive compounds flavonoids and phenolic acids, which modulate the expression of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antioxidant properties of Cracca schiedeana are attributed to the presence of phenolic compounds, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress and cellular damage. The anti-cancer properties of this plant are also reported, which are thought to be mediated by the bioactive compounds saponins and terpenoids, among others.",
