    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Cracca schiedeana are alkaloids, flavonoids, and phenolic acids. The alkaloids present in Cracca schiedeana have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which can help in the healing of wounds and infections. Flavonoids, particularly quercetin, have been reported to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, which can help in reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the body. Phenolic acids, such as ferulic acid, have been found to possess antimicrobial and antioxidant properties, which can help in protecting against microbial infections and oxidative damage. These constituents work together to provide the plant with its potential healing properties, making it a valuable resource in traditional medicine.",
